title: For Sale:  Original World War II M1 Garand
postcontent:
Gauging interest for an amazing piece of American history. I have an original World War II era Springfield Armory M1 Garand. This rifle is in amazing shape. It is chambered in 30.06 and the barrel gauge is 1, which is amazing. It has the walnut stock, which is in excellent condition for it's age. The serial number matches to a manufacture date of October 1943. I was told by the man I obtained it from that it was used by a 101st Airborne paratrooper on D-Day.

I have personally taken this rifle apart to inspect it and clean it. The stock has no internal cracks. The bolt, chamber, barrel, and internal parts all look amazing for the age of this rifle. I'm not sure why I can only post one picture, but I have more where you can clearly see that the stock has the proper "P" proof mark in the circle and the U.S. Military issue stamp on the side of the stock. 

I am debating selling this rifle, but other things in life are starting to come along (such as a possible wedding). I would be sad to see it go, because it really is an amazing piece of history. Imagine what this rifle has seen and done throughout it's lifetime. 

I am posting this to see if there is any real interest in my rifle at this point, and if I receive responses from seriously interested people, there certainly the chance it could be yours! Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  WW2 Japanese Type I rifle
postcontent:
Authentic WW2 Japanese Type I Arisaka rifle. Chambered in the original 6.5mm JAP. In great condition with cleaning rod. These are unique rifles that the Japanese Imperial Navy had manufactured under contract by the Italian gun maker solely for use by the Navy. While the Imperial Army had their Type 38's, 44's, and 99's, the Navy had the Type I.
The Type I uses the same 6.5mm JAP round that the Type 38 rifles used, and is built with many similarities to the Type 38 long rifle, except that it never had a "mum" stamped them and that these rifles were outfitted with a "carcano" type bolt action.
A great piece of WW2 history in great condition. NO import marks.

$300 Cash Firm. I strongly prefer to deal with individuals that are also OH Concealed Handgun License holders or fellow NRA Instructors. 

Additional pics upon request.
